      0 - wall
      1 - region1
      2 - region2
      3 - region3
      4 - region4
      5 - exit

        4 - region4
        5 - exit

      • getTypeInt

        public int getTypeInt()
        returns an integer representation of this tiles TileType where the integers correspond as follows:
        0 - wall
        1 - region1
        2 - region2
        3 - region3
        4 - region4
        5 - exit

        Returns:
        an integer representation of the TileType. returns a -1 if the TileType is undefined for this tile

      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object object)
        Overrides equals for the tile object. Returns true if the row and col of the given tile are equal to this tile. I based this method on some code I saw on this webpage: http://www.javamadesoeasy.com/2015/02/linkedhashmap-custom-implementation- put.html
        Overrides:
        equals in class java.lang.Object
        Parameters:
        object - The object being compared against this tile.
        Returns:
        True if the tiles are equal. False otherwise.
